712072f-a.text:
W. 33rd Street (diagonally across view from lower right corner, buildings thereon), west from Tenth Avenue (right foreground) to the North (Hudson) River. The photographer shows a general view of this West Side area that is prominently sprinkled with yards of the New York Central Railroad. In the background is the North (Hudson) Riwer and the Jersey shoreline.
December 20, 1930.
P.L. Sperr
